# Binary assets must never be treated as text.
#
# Git's text handling (and some editors/terminals/copy-paste paths) will
# "helpfully" normalise line endings or re-encode a file it believes is
# text. On a binary file that is destructive and silent: every byte that
# isn't valid UTF-8 becomes U+FFFD (ef bf bd), the file still looks about
# the right size, and nothing complains until whatever reads it fails.
#
# That is exactly what happened to assets/fonts/GentleHearts-Regular.ttf --
# ~10,000 bytes destroyed, so Qt refused to load it and the whole app
# silently fell back to a generic serif. See tests/test_font_assets.py,
# which now checks these files are still structurally intact.
*.ttf  binary
*.otf  binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.ico  binary
*.gif  binary
*.svg  text
*.db   binary
*.xlsx binary
*.xls  binary
*.docx binary
*.pdf  binary
*.msg  binary
